metrics_conclusion: Yeul's Theme has higher complexity than the average song  in terms Chord Complexity and Chord Progression Novelty.
key_conclusion:
Yeul's Theme is written in the key of C Minor.  

According to the Theorytab database, it is the 3rd most popular key among Minor keys and     the 9th most popular  among all keys. Minor keys, along with major keys, are a common choice for popular music.  The three most important chords, built off the 1st, 4th and 5th scale degrees are all minor chords (C minor, F minor, and G minor).

See the C Minor Cheat Sheet for popular chords, chord progressions, downloadable midi files and more!

metadata.editComments: Changed V7(no5b13) chords in measures 18 and 34 to V+7, and changed II7(b9) in measure 32 to V7(b9)/v.
Changed V7(#11)/ii in measure 10 to V43(b5)/VI, iv7(b5) in measure 12 to iv7 (bor), and VII11(b9) in measure 14 to V11(b9)/III.
Changed some chord labels to look cleaner and better match their functions (i.e. Bbm(b5) (phdm) in meas. 4 to Go7/Bb, because it's a Bbdim chord with a G on top and it resolves to Ab the next bar).
